<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-534-377  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 534 377.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 1 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>UK: WordPerfect ported to Unix and NeXT environments. (wordprocessing software)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gold, Steve.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   WordPerfect UK (product enhancement).andO;Product:   WordPerfect 5.0 (Word processing software) (product enhancement).andO;Topic:     EnhancementsSoftware MigrationWord processing software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>UK: WORDPERFECT PORTED TO UNIX AND NEXT ENVIRONMENTS WEYBRIDGE, SURREY,ENGLAND, 1990 OCT 1 (NB) -- Wordperfect UK has announced that version 5.0 ofits word processing package of the same name is now available for the Unixenvironment.andP;  At the same time, the company has announced a software port tothe Next computer system, the graphical user interface (GUI) intensivecomputer developed by Apple co-founder Steve Jobs.andM;Version 5.0 of Wordperfect for SCO Xenix is available for UKP425 in a singleuser configuration.andP;  Specific machine versions of WP 5.0 are under activedevelopment, with editions for machines such as the NCR Tower and IBM RS/6000series planned for the next six months.andP;  An upgrade path is available for SCOXenix v4.2 users, the company has announced.andM;The most significant enhancement seen in WP 5.0 for SCO Xenix is its abilityto import, size and rotate graphic images.andP;  In addition, a print previewfunction allows users to preview the printed page and incorporates a zoomfeature.andP;  The package parallels the DOS version of WP 5.0 right down to theuser interface, the company claims.andM;Wordperfect for Next, meanwhile, will ship during the first quarter of 1991.andO;Unlike the SCO Xenix version, WP for Next has similar features to the DOSversion, but avoids using the same user interface, preferring instead tosupport the Nextstep GUI.andP;  Pricing has yet to be confirmed.andM;Graphic placement in WP for Next is accomplished by selecting a graphic filein the browser and dragging it directly onto the document.andP;  In addition,graphical images may be placed anywhere on a page and can be scaled, movedand rotated on-screen.andP;  Other features include support for columns (newspaperand parallel), text and graphics integration, indexing, outline, macros andmerge facilities.andM;(Steve Gold/19901001/Press andamp; Public Contact: Wordperfect UK - Tel:0932-850500)</TEXT></DOC>